  "text": "To use IBMR to model surface reflectance, Wood et al. proposed the surface light field (S-LF) [CITATION_1] . Given a vertex location, e.g., a vertex index T = [u, v] which also corresponds to a specific 3D point on the object surface, we assume there is a ray along the direction D i = [d i x , d i y , d i z ] hitting at T and its corresponding reflection ray leaves along D o , the angle between D i and D o is θ .",
